AUDIO: 'a sensor placed far away and transmitted over long distance. Now, imagine this, you place this system in a completely remote location, no internet, no'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'infrastructure, and still you can monitor everything in real time. But, here\'s where things get really interesting. Think about this for a second, most smart systems today depend'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on Wi-Fi or Bluetooth, but in real life, that\'s a big limitation. Bluetooth usually works within 10 to 30 m, and Wi-Fi typically covers around 50 to 100'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'm. And the bigger problem, many important places don\'t even have internet access, places like farms, remote warehouses, construction sites, mountain areas. In these locations,'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'running cables is expensive and sometimes not even possible. So, instead of relying on internet, we use LoRa. LoRa is built for long-range communication. It can send data over'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'several kilometers using very low power, which means your system stays connected even where everything else fails. Now, that solves the communication part, but'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what about detection? This is the RD days 03D mmWave radar module. Unlike traditional PIR sensors, it doesn\'t rely on heat or light. It uses radio waves to detect movement, and it\'s not like other'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mmWave radar modules, you can set its detection mode and track up to three moving targets at the same time. It works in complete darkness, in fog. It can even see through many materials,'

[02:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cardboard, plastic, hardboard, glass, curtains,'

[02:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'even wood, and many more. And it can detect even the smallest movements. It\'s a true human presence sensor. Standing still, sitting, or even crawling, you can\'t'

[02:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hide from it. Now, combine both technologies and you get something incredibly powerful, a system that can detect movement in real time, track presence accurately, send data over'

[02:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'kilometers, and work without any internet. On the receiver side, we will monitor important data like XY position, distance, angle, and speed on an OLED display, but that\'s not all. I have also'

[03:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'created a real radar-style interface, where you can visually see the exact position of the detected person. For those who don\'t want to use a computer, I have implemented the same radar'

